            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="sandhist"></a>Sanderstead Local History Group. Monthly on a Wednesday</h3>
                <p>Want to discover more local history? If so then 'The Sanderstead Local History Group' would like to invite you to our monthly meetings held 2-4pm at All Saints Church Hall Onslow Gardens Sanderstead the last Wednesday in the month. A small charge of £2 each meeting to cover hall hire and refreshments. No annual fee. Information is on the Bourne Society website re the area covered and local history books they have produced plus details of the SLHG meetings.</p>
                    <p>Contact Joyce Hoad (Chair) joycehoad@virginmedia.com or chris.harman@tiscali.co.uk</p>
                </td>
                <td class="events">
                <h3><%= link_to "Bourne Society", "http://bournesoc.org.uk/" %></h3>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <tr>
              <td class="events">
                <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="soul"></a>Soul Symphony Choir, Tuesday evenings at 7pm</h3>
                <p>Soul Symphony Choir is a fun, friendly and vibrant choir based in Croydon. ‘I love everyone’s positivity and how wonderful everyone’s attitude is. Every week you have a rehearsal to look forward to with what feels like a second family,’ Lizzy. Be energised by our uplifting sessions as well as the mutual support and encouragement of the Soul Symphony Choir community. Come join us – free taster for your first session.</p>
                <p>For more information please visit www.soulsymphony.co.uk or email info@soulsymphony.co.uk</p>
                 <p>You are welcome to join us on Tuesday evenings from 7pm at St Columba’s Church, 37 Queenhill Road, South Croydon CR2 8DW. For more information please visit <%= link_to "www.soulsymphony.co.uk", "http://www.soulsymphony.co.uk" %>.</p>
               </td>
